        <safety>
          <warning>
            Failure to secure gear position before actuator removal may cause uncontrolled gear movement, resulting in injury or airframe damage.
          </warning>
          <caution>
            Do not reuse actuator bolts or hydraulic seals. Always replace with new parts per IPC and AMM torque values.
          </caution>
          <note>
            This task requires follow-up functional gear swing test and hydraulic leak check after reinstallation (Ref: AMM 32-00-00-710-801).
          </note>
        </safety>
      </preliminaryRqmts>

      <mainProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Access MLG downlock actuator zone through panel 615AR (Ref: AMM 06-00-00 ZONE 700).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Install gear downlock pin (PN: TOOL-GEARLOCK-777) in actuator clevis to secure MLG in down position.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Tag and disconnect hydraulic lines (INLET, OUTLET) from actuator. Cap and plug all ports with approved contamination prevention caps.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Remove actuator attachment bolts (Qty 2, PN: NAS6204U) and discard. Support actuator during removal.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Inspect clevis, actuator yoke bushings, and hydraulic fittings for wear or distortion. Refer to AMM 32-00-00-220-801 for acceptance criteria.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Install replacement actuator (PN: ACT-DL-M777). Use new fasteners and torque to 125 in-lb. Apply torque seal.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Reconnect hydraulic lines using new O-rings (MS29513-123). Torque per AMM 20-50-00.</para>
        </step>
      </mainProcedure>

      <closeProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Remove downlock pin. Restore hydraulic pressure to system B. Perform landing gear extension/retraction test per AMM 32-00-00-710-801.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Check actuator and line connections for leakage during system pressure application.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Record actuator serial number, installation date, and leak test results in gear configuration logbook.</para>
        </step>
      </closeProcedure>

