          <para>Visually inspect wear indicator pin for engagement. If flush or recessed, perform calibrated depth measurement.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Insert brake wear gauge tool (PN: GAUGE-WP-777) into access slot. Gently push tool until seated. Do not force.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Read calibrated scale. If wear exceeds 0.180 inches (minimum allowable thickness), tag brake for replacement (Ref: CMM 32-41-01).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>If wear pin shows incorrect projection, remove and replace pin (PN: PIN-WEAR-77A) using 3/8" torque driver set to 35 in-lb.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Install new pin. Ensure spring detent engages. Apply torque seal to indicator base threads.</para>
        </step>
      </mainProcedure>

