  <content>
    <procedure>
      <preliminaryRqmts>
        <preliminaryRqmtsDescr>Aircraft jacked and leveled (Ref: AMM 08-10-00). Main gear removed. Hydraulic and nitrogen systems depressurized and vented.</preliminaryRqmtsDescr>
        <safety>
          <warning>
            Shock strut contains pressurized nitrogen and hydraulic fluid. Ensure complete depressurization before removing gland nut. Failure to do so may cause explosion or injury.
          </warning>
          <caution>
            Use only approved seal replacement kits (PN: SEALKIT-MLG-777). Unapproved O-rings may degrade under Skydrol or MIL-H-5606 fluids.
          </caution>
          <note>
            This task requires strut stroke and fluid level to be verified after assembly. See AMM 12-15-01-600-801 for final servicing.
          </note>
        </safety>
      </preliminaryRqmts>

      <mainProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Place MLG assembly in hydraulic maintenance stand (PN: STRUT-CRADLE-777). Ensure full stability and clamping.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Open nitrogen charging valve and bleed gas completely. Observe pressure drop to zero on servicing gauge.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Remove safety wire from gland nut. Mark alignment line across strut barrel and gland.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Use gland nut spanner wrench (PN: TOOL-GLAND-777) to loosen and remove gland. Collect escaping hydraulic fluid in certified waste pan.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Withdraw piston rod carefully. Inspect inner barrel for scoring, pitting, or O-ring fragments. Clean bore with solvent CPC#472 and lint-free cloth.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Remove and discard used seals, scraper ring, back-up rings, and wear rings from piston and gland. Inspect for uneven wear or damage.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Install new seals using seal pusher tool (PN: TOOL-SEALPUSH-777). Lubricate with approved strut fluid (BMS 3-11 Type IV).</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Reinstall piston into strut. Align marks and torque gland nut to 220 ft-lb. Safety wire in place.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Refill strut with hydraulic fluid per AMM 12-15-01-600-801. Charge with nitrogen to target pressure. Measure static extension.</para>
        </step>
      </mainProcedure>

      <closeProcedure>
        <step>
          <para>Clean exterior of strut. Apply corrosion inhibitor if paint barrier compromised.</para>
        </step>
        <step>
          <para>Document seal kit part number, strut SN, final fluid type, and nitrogen pressure in aircraft maintenance record.</para>
        </step>
      </closeProcedure>

